# Team hero layout (always)

Every team page header is **one** `TeamHeroCard`. The coach picks one of **six**
approved compositions in the builder (Hero settings → "Header layout").
**Content never changes between variants** — cover, logo, name, subtitle, city, Live,
social links only. Only placement changes.

## The six approved variants (`HeroLayoutVariant`)

See **Header Variants** reference mockup — do not invent new layouts.

1. `inside_header` — logo and team name **on the cover photo** (bottom row).
2. `overlap_large` (**default**) — large logo **centered** on the cover edge, name below.
3. `circle_on_header` — logo in a **frosted circle** on the photo, name beside it.
4. `inline` — logo left overlapping, name **beside** it on the right.
5. `square` — **square** logo frame for complex marks, text to the right.
6. `minimal` — **no logo**; name and optional meta on the cover gradient.

Legacy IDs (`stack`, `center`, `overlay`) map via `resolveHeroVariant()` — never auto-pick.

Variant is stored in hero settings as `heroLayout` and read via `resolveHeroVariant()`.
Root gets a modifier class `hero-card--{variant}` (see `heroVariantClass()`).

## Hero content limit

Cover · logo (except `minimal`) · team name · optional subtitle · optional location · social links.
**Nothing else** — no description, motto, stats, athlete counts, or profile metadata in the hero.

## Mandatory rules

- One source of truth: `TeamHeroCard` / `BlockHero`. Never duplicate hero markup in the builder preview.
- Variants are **CSS modifiers** on `.hero-card`. Small JSX branches only where placement differs (`cover-identity`, `overlay-text`, inline spacer).
- Shared primitives: `hero-card__cover`, `hero-card__logo-anchor`, `hero-card__title/subtitle/city`, `hero-card__cover-identity`, `hero-card__overlay-text`.
- Overlap variants (`overlap_large`, `inline`, `square`): logo anchor inside cover with `translateY(50%)`; body padding clears the logo's lower half.
- `inline` / `square`: `hero-card__logo-spacer` + `hero-card__text-zone`.
- `inside_header` / `circle_on_header`: logo + title in `hero-card__cover-identity`; body holds subtitle, city, social only.
- `minimal`: title + optional meta in `hero-card__overlay-text`; body holds social only if present.
- Cover `z-index: 2` · body `z-index: 1` so the logo paints above the white band.
- Use **container queries** on `.hero-card` (`team-hero`), not viewport `@media`.
- Default logo is **circular**; `square` variant uses rounded-square frame.
- Cover height **160–180px** mobile via `--hero-cover-height` (~10.5rem).
- Page must look premium with only logo + cover + team name.

## Do not

- Invent new hero layouts or auto-pick variants.
- Add metadata, counters, or profile-style rows to fill empty space.
- Add per-variant data fields — all variants share the same content.
- Duplicate layout in builder preview — use `TeamHeroCard` / `BlockHero`.

